# Script version history

When editing any tracked script or profile file, add a new **top** history line (newest first). Do not edit older lines.

## Format (all files)

```bash
# v. YYYYMMDD.HH24MISS - brief what changed
```

- Use local time at edit time (`date +%Y%m%d.%H%M%S`).
- One short description after the dash.
- Shell scripts: immediately after the shebang.
- `bashrc`, `bash_profile`: at file top (no shebang).
- When `bashrc` or `bash_profile` changes, also add a matching top line to `.pgm-bundle-version`.

## After changes

Commit and push to `master` unless the user says otherwise.
